<TITLE> Manik's national unity dream could solve crisis: leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)--A meaningful change to the present political situation could be forged through greater national unity, realising the dream of the late veteran politician Saifuddin Ahmed Manik, national leaders said Tuesday. Leaders of different political parties made the call for change at a citizens' memorial meeting for Manikone of the prominent communist leaderswho died Feb 3. "Without national unity, no individual leader can rid the nation of the present situation," Jatiya Samajtantrik Dal president ASM Abdur Rab said at the memorial meeting held at the Institution of Engineers, Bangladesh. Dr Kamal Hossain, president of Gano Forum, said: "There is no alternative to greater unity. Meaningful change has to be brought in the country to materialise the dream of Saifuddin Ahmed Manik." Manik was a founding member and general secretary of Gano Forum. "Saifuddin Ahmed Manik did politics in the national interest rising above personal and party interest. To materialise his dream we have to work together," Awami League presidium member Amir Hossain Amu said. Communist Party of Bangladesh general secretary Mujahidul Islam Selim said of the former CPB leader: "Saifuddin Ahmed Manik was not ready to deviate from his principles for even a moment. We found him one of our comrades until the last day of his life." bdnews
